Package jkarel

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Beeper
    The Beeper is a renderable object that keeps track of its location on the world and it's number of beepers.
    Box
    The Box is a renderable object that keeps (or supply) beepers.
    Coordinate
    Coordinate is a basic container for two ints representing the x and y coordinates of some object.
    Debug
    Debug provides an easy way for all components of the client to output various levels of debug information, from full to error, only having to change the debug level the client is run in.
    Item
    The Item class keeps track of an x and y coordinate and provides an abstract render method.
    Robot
    The Robot defines robot attributes and actions.
    Wall
    A Wall is a barrier that is rendered on the WorldPanel.
    World
    World houses most of the static constants used in object creation and rendering, Karel file locations and images, and the speed at which the WorldPanel updates.
    WorldBackend
    WorldBackend - define world backend item and actions.
    WorldFrame
    WorldFrame houses the WorldPanel and deals with its creation using the WorldBackend passed to the constructor.
    WorldPanel
    The WorldPanel is responsible for actually drawing the world, according to the specifications of the associated WorldBackend.
